    "methodology": "SDEC attendances count patients seen in same-day emergency care units — ambulatory care settings where patients can be assessed, diagnosed, and treated without overnight admission. The conversion rate is the proportion of emergency attendances handled via SDEC pathways rather than traditional overnight admission. A&E four-hour performance measures the percentage of patients spending four hours or less in A&E from arrival to admission, transfer, or discharge. Average length of stay is measured in hours for SDEC patients only. All figures are for England.",
